node.text: @rezhermanto aint no robot man, i need to watch my netflix series at 5 PM sharp! 🤣
Won't be complaining about being in office ever again...
No but honestly, I think some mix of the 2 is a great way to go. So many Singaporean children don't grow up with their parents. Having a flexible arrangement is one way we can change that
@mswwfslife the little girl look like u sia hahahaha
LOL hope my mum enjoys my company even though I'm not a kid
I wouldn’t mind either, just that I would want my break time to be able to go out of my FKING HOUSE
After CB the kids will go school already mah, so all heavenly again haha
Crazy! Electricity & water bills will be high!

If we start working from home, think about it. That means there is no reason to go to a location to sit for a few hours to do their jobs. Instead, who knows, you could be doing your job but maybe in japan indtead of singapore, but it doesn't matter bcos you are still doing your job. This kinda allows us to go anywhere to do their jobs.
Of course they prefer to work home.. home got no printer, no scanner.. all email to office and get the work done.. F M L
